  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention of the Transmission of COVID-19 and the Reduction of the Community Tensions Linked to COVID-19 in High Risk Border Areas of the Central African Republic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to help prevent the local transmission of COVID-19 by raising awareness among populations particularly exposed in the border areas in the Central African Republic (CAR). Concretely, it aims to increase information and awareness to access prevention and treatment services for COVID-19. The project is implemented in close collaboration with the national committee for the management of the COVID-19 crisis and is necessary because of disinformation and rumors that reduce the effectiveness of the COVID-19 control programs implemented by the Ministry of Health. By targeting populations particularly vulnerable to COVID-19, people with pre-existing diseases such as diabetics, tuberculosis patients and people living with HIV with a view to heightened awareness and referral to health services available, the project contributes to a targeted response to COVID-19 in CAR.</narrative>
  </description>
